18:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Fotor AI and Kaiber share a solid foundation of core features including Text To Image, Image To Image, Style Transfer, Commercial License. Where Fotor AI pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Inpainting and Outpainting and Upscaling, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Fotor AI holds an overall score of 5/10 and an ease of use score of 8/10, while Kaiber scores 6/10 overall and 7/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
19:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Fotor AI offers a more budget-friendly entry point at Free, compared to Kaiber's starting price of $10/mo. Fotor AI has a notable advantage here with its free plan, allowing you to get started without any financial commitment. Kaiber does not currently offer a free tier, which means you will need to pay from day one."}]]}]
